<sec>
<st>
Personal background</st>

<p>

Fellner went to <school wordnetid="108276720" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../381/2188381.xml">
Cranleigh School</link></school>
 in Surrey, England from 1972-77. He attended the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../426/88426.xml">
Guildhall School of Music and Drama</link> in London.  He is a good friend of <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<film_maker wordnetid="110088390" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../779/170779.xml">
Hugh Grant</link></actor>
</film_maker>
</person>
, who is the star of some of Working Title's biggest box office hits.  Fellner and his long-time partner, model <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../119/2135119.xml">
Laura Bailey</link>, have two children together.</p>
<p>

He was awarded the C.B.E. (Commander of the <order wordnetid="107168623" confidence="0.8">
<event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<command wordnetid="107168131" confidence="0.8">
<act wordnetid="100030358" confidence="0.8">
